CSS Guide

Adding CSS:
	1) Inline CSS:				(pls dont use)
			Directly in Html

	2) Internal CSS:
			Using <style> tags within the document.

	3) External CSS: 
			Linking an external .css file

note:	priority level
		
		inline > internal > External

		-> to see external css working remove/comment inline and internal
		-> to see internal css working remove/comment inline css

Format:

	a {	background-color: yellow; }

	a 				 -> Selector
	{ 				 -> declaration
	background-color -> property
	:				 -> property/value seperator
	yellow			 -> value
	;				 -> declaration seperator
	}				 -> declaration end


Colors in CSS:

	-> color Names:
		eg:
			body{
				color: red;
			}

	-> HTML5 color names:
		eg:
			body{
				background: coral;
			}

	-> Hexadecimal:	
		eg:
			h1{
				color: #00ff00
			}
		(first 2 for red, middle 2 for green, last 2 for blue)

	-> RGB: (in decimal)
		eg:
			p{
				color: rgb(0,0,255)
			}

Fonts:
	
	use Web Safe Fonts.

ID vs CLASS:
	
	ID -> for unique element. two same id not possible.
	class -> same styling can be used elsewhere.


BOX model:
	
	content-> content of page.
	padding-> space between content and border.
	border -> 
	margin -> space outside

		p{
			margin-top:5px;
			margin-bottom:5px;
			margin-right:10px;
			margin-left:10px;
		}

		or

		p{
			margin: 5px 10px  5px    10px;
					top right bottom left
		}

		or 

		p{
			margin: 5px 		10px;
					top&bottom  left&right
		}


CSS Positioning:

	Static: Default settings.

	Relative: Relative to this positioning others would work.

	Absolute: Its fixed with respective. the relative.

	Fixed: Fixed position with the browser.

	note:: If you cant understant what the above means pls see a youtube video.

